=  AllDependencies =

Recursivelly show all dependencies for a given program and version in an (optional) nice tree view. Recursivelly means that it will also show the dependencies for each dependency detected, and so on.

Usage: AllDependencies <package> [<version>]

Options:
* '''-h, --help''' - Shows this help.
* '''-v, --version''' - Show program version.
* '''-V, --verbose''' - Enable verbose mode.
* '''-t, --tree''' - Hierarchic view.
* '''-L, --no-list''' - Don't use the 'cached' dependency file, recompute everything.
* '''-r, --repeat''' - Allow repeated entries (circular dependencies will loop endlessly!)

Examples:
<blockquote>
AllDependencies -t -r GTK+ <br/>
</blockquote>

